Description: Limestone ostracon: on one side only, a black ink drawing of Horus falcon wearing double crown.
Curator's comments: For the subject cf. O. IFAO 2996 in J.Vandier d'Abbadie, 'J. Vandier d'Abbadie, 'Catalogue des ostraca figurés de Deir el Médineh' II 4(Cairo, 1959), p. 219, pl. CXLIX; and O. Cairo 25195 in G. Daressy, 'Ostraca' (Cairo, 1901), p. 37, pl. XXXIII.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Somerset Lowry-Corry, 2nd Earl of Belmore
